generalComment.value:
"This EPD is based on primary data for those aspects that are considered crucial, such as the type of raw materials used and the composition of the products examined, the distances between raw material suppliers and the production site, and the plant's energy consumption.

For all processes for which primary data are not available, secondary data taken from the LCA Ecoinvent v3.8, Allocation, Cut off by Classification database was used.

As required by the PCRs ""Construction Products and Construction Services"" the use of generic data (proxy data) has been limited and their contribution does not exceed 10% of the total impact."


"For virgin raw materials, both the impacts associated with the materials themselves and those associated with the related production processes were considered.

With regard to raw materials of recycled origin, only the impacts of the recycling process are considered. Outputs subject to recycling are considered inputs to the next life cycle.

Some impacts of the production plant (e.g., electricity, water and diesel consumption) have been allocated among the outputs of the 2021 production on an economic basis.

There is no difference in modeling between the two processes with ""dry load"" and ""pre-mixed load."" As a result, water consumption, electricity consumption, diesel consumption of truck mixers, and emissions produced were allocated equally without distinguishing between the two production lines."


The cut-off rules in EN 15804:2019 have been applied, the applied cut-offs do not exceed 1% of the mass and energy flows entering the system.

technologicalApplicability.value:
"Multibeton XC concretes are specifically formulated to vary within a broad range, considering factors such as mechanical strength requirements, environmental conditions of the construction site, and casting complexity. They are particularly recommended for constructions where the reinforcement is exposed to air and moisture, thereby posing a risk of carbonation-induced reinforcement bar corrosion. 
 The concretes produced by Betonrossi S.p.a. at its production site in Piacenza are mixtures of water, cement, aggregates of different sizes and additives.
